<Base
  title="Affiliate Disclosure — BuilderSoftwareGuide"
  description="BuilderSoftwareGuide earns affiliate commissions from some software links. Here's exactly how that works and how it does (and doesn't) affect our recommendations."
>
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prose">
        <div class="meta">Legal</div>
        <h1>Affiliate Disclosure</h1>
        <p>We're transparent about how we earn money. Here's exactly what you need to know.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-body">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prose">

        <h2>We earn commissions from some links</h2>
        <p>BuilderSoftwareGuide participates in affiliate programs with some of the software vendors we review. This means that if you click a link on our site and sign up for a software subscription, we may receive a commission from the vendor at no additional cost to you.</p>

        <p>Affiliate relationships we currently have (or are pursuing) include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Buildertrend</strong> — We are in the process of joining the Buildertrend Ambassador Program. Links to Buildertrend are marked <code>rel="nofollow sponsored"</code>.</li>
          <li><strong>Houzz Pro</strong> — Houzz Pro runs an affiliate program (approximately 10% of first-year subscription revenue). Links are marked accordingly.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Platforms we review that have <strong>no affiliate relationship</strong> with us include Procore, Fieldwire, and JobTread. We cover these because they're relevant to our readers — not because we earn money from them.</p>

        <h2>How affiliate relationships affect (and don't affect) our content</h2>
        <p>We maintain editorial independence. Affiliate commissions don't determine our rankings, recommendations, or the content of our reviews. We would rather give you an honest recommendation that doesn't earn us money than a biased one that does.</p>

        <p>Specifically:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>We do not accept payment for positive reviews or rankings.</li>
          <li>We disclose affiliate links clearly on all pages where they appear.</li>
          <li>We list real pricing, real cons, and real limitations even for software we earn commissions from.</li>
          <li>We recommend non-affiliated software when it's the right fit for the reader.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>FTC compliance</h2>
        <p>In accordance with FTC guidelines (16 C.F.R. Part 255), we disclose material connections between us and the brands whose products we mention. Affiliate links are our primary monetization mechanism and constitute a material connection.</p>

        <h2>Questions?</h2>
        <p>If you have questions about our affiliate relationships or editorial process, email us at <a href="mailto:team@buildersoftwareguide.com">team@buildersoftwareguide.com</a>.</p>

        <p style="margin-top:2rem; font-size:0.9rem; color:var(--c-muted);">Last updated: April 2026</p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
